dialog{
  id = "puzzletest.3sign",
  text = [[
Press the key you used to activate the ability again in order to "lock" the targeting system which allows you to freely move your mouse without changing where you are targeting.
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "puzzletest.4sign",
  text = [[
In puzzle levels, you can't throw the sword over walls. However, you can throw the sword over, for example, a pit of lava.
NEWSCREEN
Archers will wait before firing arrows as a special ability. The normal ability won't wait.
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "sequencetest.1",
  text = [[
Don't do it!
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "sequencetest.2",
  text = [[
This war has gone on for far too long. 
There has been too many casualties. 
We have no choice but to call upon the power of the sword.
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "sequencetest.3",
  text = [[
This isn't just your sacrifice!
According to the legends, over 500 soldiers lost their souls during the previous war.
If you take this sword, you will sacrifice our entire army!
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "sequencetest.4",
  text = [[
That's a sacrifice I'm willing to make.
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "sequencetest.4.1",
  text = [[
Skeletons - how did they manage to get this far into town?
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "sequencetest.4.2",
  text = [[
No matter - once we have awoken the sword, we won't have to worry about our defenses.
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "sequencetest.5",
  text = [[
I'm going to pick it up.
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "sequencetest.6",
  text = [[
Aaaaarggghhhh!
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "sequencetest.7",
  text = [[
What have you done!?
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "sequencetest.8",
  text = [[
...
NEWSCREEN
(Use ${up}, ${left}, ${down}, and ${right} to move.)
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "sequencetest.cleric_afterwards",
  text = [[
Hello Mr. Sword, please don't kill me.
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "test",
  text = [[
Hello player!
Welcome to the Solarus
sample quest.
There is not much to
play yet, but any help
is very appreciated!
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "title_screen.press_space",
  text = [[
Press The Space Bar
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "tutorial.1",
  text = [[
Defeating the Demon Lord with the Demon Lord's sword? This has got to be the stupidest idea I have ever heard.
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "tutorial.2",
  text = [[
We only won the last war because of the power of the Demon Sword.
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "tutorial.3",
  text = [[
Yeah, but this time we're fighting the Demon Lord. How do we know the Demon Sword isn't going to betray us?
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "tutorial.4",
  text = [[
Huh, I didn't think of that.
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "tutorial.5",
  text = [[
Anyway, what's with the signs around here? Like, what does "Press ${normal}" even mean?
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "tutorial.6",
  text = [[
What I want to know is why a sign is telling me how to read signs.
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "tutorial.bard",
  text = [[
These signs are really bothering me.
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "tutorial.knight",
  text = [[
I think a couple of skeletons walked past us while we were talking ...
NEWSCREEN
Well, it's probably fine.
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "tutorial.sign1",
  text = [[
Press ${normal} to read signs. You probably already knew that, though.
NEWSCREEN
You can also press ${normal} to talk to people.
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "tutorial.sign2",
  text = [[
Press ${normal} to use your normal attack. For most people, the normal attack is to swing a sword. You can check what your normal ability is by looking at the left-most icon at the bottom.
NEWSCREEN
Use your mouse cursor to aim. You will attack in the direction of your mouse cursor.
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "tutorial.sign3",
  text = [[
You must defeat all enemies before you can leave a map.
NEWSCREEN
You can tell someone is an enemy when they look like they are up to no good.
NEWSCREEN
Enemies also have a red lifebar above them, so you can use that too.
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "tutorial2.knight",
  text = [[
I keep throwing these swords like the sign tells me to, but nothings happening!
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "tutorial2.sign1",
  text = [[
To go over this cliff, use ${throwallies} to throw your sword.
This will pass your sword to the closest ally to your mouse pointer.
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "tutorial2.sign2",
  text = [[
Your special ability is displayed in the rightmost icon.
Use ${special} to use your special ability.
NEWSCREEN
Many abilities have a casting time, where there is a delay between the starting the ability and using the ability.
Many abilities also have a cooldown time, where the ability can't be used again until the timer ends.
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "tutorial2.sign3",
  text = [[
I spent years of research creating this combat dummy.
It's completely invincible!
NEWSCREEN
Unless it's hit by an axe.
Its one weakness..
NEWSCREEN
The third icon is your Sword Transformation ability.
Use ${swordtransform} to transform your sword.
Then use ${normal} to swing it. 
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "tutorial2.sign4",
  text = [[
Hold down ${abilityhelp} to see a description of your abilities.
It will also pause time while you're reading it.
NEWSCREEN
Be sure to not misuse this power or you will cause a time paradox.
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "tutorial3.sign",
  text = [[
You should not use ${block} to defend yourself.
Defense is for losers.
Winners use only offensive moves.
]]
}

dialog{
  id = "tutorial3.sign2",
  text = [[
The blue bar is the adventurer's soul.
NEWSCREEN
The adventurer's soul gets weaker the longer they are possessed.
This means you do less damage.
The soul will heal naturally if you stop possessing that person.
NEWSCREEN
If your soul bar gets low, switch to a different person!
]]
}

